The length of these movements can indicate the level of cognitive effort required to process the information. Longer saccade lengths may indicate that the code is more complex or requires more effort to comprehend., Gaze location: Eye tracking can also provide information about where the developer is looking on the screen. If the developer is fixating on irrelevant parts of the screen or is not able to locate important parts of the code, this may indicate that the code is difficult to navigate or comprehend., Reading speed: Eye tracking can also provide information about reading speed. If the developer is reading slowly or is frequently pausing to re-read sections of code, this may indicate that the code is difficult to comprehend.
